2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the construction of linear codes using puncturing and shortening of cyclic codes, which involves the manipulation of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to the study of network coding and communication in social and information networks. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve the analysis of the computational complexity of constructing linear codes using puncturing and shortening of cyclic codes. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper may involve the application of discrete mathematics in the study of cyclic codes and their properties.
